BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:HHitbCzIxgt7-9luusT2W
SUMMARY:SP 202: Fabric Printing
DTSTAMP:20260314T160740Z
DTSTART:20260314T190000Z
DESCRIPTION:Do you dream of people wearing your artwork out on the streets?
	 Want to make shirts for your friend’s music project? Level up your fabric
	 printing experience and take home your own printed tote bag in this 3-hou
	r intermediate-level fabric printing class! In this hands-on workshop\, yo
	u’ll explore the use-cases for printing on fabric\, practice properly sett
	ing up on the t-shirt press\, and understand different types of fabrics an
	d inks. Students will receive three tote bags to print on\, or have the op
	tion to bring their own light-colored 100% cotton fabrics to practice on. 
	Students will be printing a Vera specific design\, exclusive to the 202 cl
	ass.\n\nStudents must complete Screenprint 101 before attending this class
	.\n\nhttps://link.dice.fm/B75453a3bdb7\n\nFrom The Vera Project
URL:https://link.dice.fm/B75453a3bdb7
LOCATION:305 Harrison Street\, Seattle\, Washington 98109\, United States
X-CALRIPPER-SOURCE:vera-project
CATEGORIES:The Vera Project
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT3H
END:VEVENT
